---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Work - Anastasia Bessonova"
  description="Selected narrative design and screenwriting work across games, animation, and corporate projects."
>
  <section class="block reading flow">
    <h1>Work</h1>
    <p>
      Selected projects across game narrative design, animation, and corporate storytelling.
      Some details are redacted or generalised due to NDA.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- TSAREVNA -->
  <section class="section block reading flow">
    <h2>Tsarevna — Dark Fantasy Action Game</h2>
    <p class="muted">Watt Studio · PC (Steam) · Released 2026</p>
    <p>
      Narrative designer and screenwriter on a dark fantasy action game. Responsible for lore development,
      character design and backstories, quest design, and integrating narrative with game design.
    </p>
    <p>
      Developed a dual-character dynamic between the Princess and her companion/reflection to create
      layered narrative tension and emotional resonance, moving beyond standard genre archetypes.
      Player discussions highlight the protagonists' relationship and world lore as standout strengths.
    </p>
    <p class="links">
      <a href="/work/tsarevna">Full case study →</a>
      <a href="https://store.steampowered.com/app/3348640/Tsarevna/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Steam page ↗</a>
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- GRIMPS -->
  <section class="section block reading flow">
    <h2>Grimps (formerly Plushies) — Comedic Shooter</h2>
    <p class="muted">Watt Studio · PC (Steam) · Released</p>
    <p>
      Screenwriter from concept phase. Responsible for concept development, lore creation,
      character design, pilot episode script, and in-game dialogue.
    </p>
    <p>
      Led audience research segmenting the 7–12 age range by psychological motivations,
      using those insights to design a cast where each character directly reflected
      a different player/viewer profile, ensuring broad appeal without feeling generic.
    </p>
    <p class="links">
      <a href="https://store.steampowered.com/app/3297800/GRIMPS/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Steam page ↗</a>
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- ETG GROUP -->
  <section class="section block reading flow">
    <h2>ETG Group — Interactive Novel for HR</h2>
    <p class="muted">Storyworks · Web · Released</p>
    <p>
      Lead narrative designer and scriptwriter on a branching interactive novel for employee
      onboarding. Developed the full narrative: concept, characters, branching script, and dialogue,
      transforming mandatory HR materials into a choice-driven story.
    </p>
    <p>
      The project replaced static onboarding documents and demonstrated measurable efficacy
      of gamified narrative for corporate learning, leading to commissions from further clients
      including Moscow Currency Exchange and Mosinzhproekt.
    </p>
    <p class="links">
      <a href="https://adventure.emergingtravel.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">View project ↗</a>
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- ANIMATION -->
  <section class="section block reading flow">
    <h2>Animation — Screenwriter & Editor</h2>
    <p class="muted">Multiple studios · Ongoing</p>
    <p>
      Over a decade writing for leading animation studios including RIKI Group (Smeshariki, Pin Code,
      Dino City, Fixies), Parovoz (Leo and Tig, Katya and Ef), Metrafilms (Lex and Plu),
      Soyuzmultfilm, Agama Film, Delai, and Vidimo.
    </p>
    <p>
      Regular participant in writers' rooms and series development, contributing to season arcs,
      character development, and episode brainstorming for series including Sport School, Monsiki,
      and the international co-production Sante & Tropica. Also served in editorial and story
      development roles, overseeing narrative consistency and leading pilot development for new projects.
    </p>
    <p class="links">
      <a href="https://www.kinopoisk.ru/name/4733697/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Kinopoisk filmography ↗</a>
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- THEOREMKIN -->
  <section class="section block reading flow">
    <h2>Theoremkin Studios — Brand Narrative & Character System</h2>
    <p class="muted">Corporate / Brand · Released, ongoing</p>
    <p>
      Lead narrative architect for a network of children's speech therapy studios.
      Developed the overarching lore, core character system, and personality frameworks
      that transformed educational exercises into an adventure-based brand experience.
    </p>
    <p>
      Children become "agents" solving missions, guided by a cast of companion characters
      each aligned with different learning stages. The system scaled into copybooks, merchandise,
      studio opening programmes, and internal documents, becoming the core of the brand's identity.
    </p>
    <p class="muted" style="font-size:0.9em;">NDA — client name can be mentioned, specific assets private.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- SIBUR -->
  <section class="section block reading flow">
    <h2>SIBUR — Corporate Culture Interactive Landing</h2>
    <p class="muted">Storyworks · Web · Released</p>
    <p>
      Narrative designer, copywriter, and UX concept co-creator on an interactive landing page
      for SIBUR's 30th anniversary. Co-created a framing narrative featuring an alien visitor
      discovering the company's culture, making employer values accessible, humorous, and memorable.
    </p>
    <p>
      Designed and wrote gamified elements including personality quizzes and interactive stories.
      The result became a standalone cultural hub embedded in the recruitment site.
    </p>
    <p class="links">
      <a href="https://www.infografika.agency/cases/lending-o-korporativnoy-kulture" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">View case ↗</a>
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- ORIGINAL IP -->
  <section class="section block reading flow">
    <h2>Original Teen Sci-Fi/Fantasy Series & Game — Transmedia IP</h2>
    <p class="muted">In development · Pitch stage</p>
    <p>
      Creator, creative producer, and narrative designer on an original transmedia project
      combining a series and game concept. The story centres on adolescents who undergo a
      literal tripartite metamorphosis, exploring identity, integration, and connection
      through a sci-fi/fantasy lens.
    </p>
    <p>
      Leading a collaborative team of writers and artists. Deliverables include a full series bible,
      pilot script, game concept document, and pitch deck. Private materials available for
      pitch presentations.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- WRITING SAMPLES -->
  <section class="section block reading flow">
    <h2>Writing samples</h2>
    <p class="muted">
      Available on request while NDA-safe public excerpts are being prepared.
    </p>
  </section>

  <style>
    .muted { color: var(--muted); }
    .links { display: flex; gap: 16px; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-top: 0.5rem; }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>
